{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"5365","heading":"General provisions","label":"5365 General provisions","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/ch46/schIV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Prior ProvisionsA prior section 5365, , as added , , , related to reports, prior to repeal by , , . See . Such section was formerly classified to prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as section 5365.Pub. L. 93–638, title IV, § 405Pub. L. 103–413, title II, § 204108 Stat. 4276Pub. L. 116–180, title I, § 101(e)134 Stat. 864section 5372 of this titlesection 458ee of this titleOct. 25, 1994Oct. 21, 2020"],"amendments":["Prior ProvisionsA prior section 5365, , as added , , , related to reports, prior to repeal by , , . See . Such section was formerly classified to prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as section 5365.Pub. L. 93–638, title IV, § 405Pub. L. 103–413, title II, § 204108 Stat. 4276Pub. L. 116–180, title I, § 101(e)134 Stat. 864section 5372 of this titlesection 458ee of this titleOct. 25, 1994Oct. 21, 2020"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Applicability","label":"a Applicability","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"An Indian Tribe and the Secretary shall include in any compact or funding agreement provisions that reflect the requirements of this subchapter.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Conflicts of interest","label":"b Conflicts of interest","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"An Indian Tribe participating in self-governance shall ensure that internal measures are in place to address, pursuant to Tribal law and procedures, conflicts of interest in the administration of programs.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Audits","label":"c Audits","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Single Agency Audit Act","label":"1 Single Agency Audit Act","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Chapter 75 of title 31 shall apply to a funding agreement under this subchapter.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Cost principles","label":"2 Cost principles","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any provision of law, including ; orsection 5325 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any exemptions to applicable Office of Management and Budget circulars subsequently granted by the Office of Management and Budget.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Federal claims","label":"3 Federal claims","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Any claim by the Federal Government against an Indian Tribe relating to funds received under a funding agreement based on any audit under this subsection shall be subject to .section 5325(f) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Redesign and consolidation","label":"d Redesign and consolidation","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"so long as the redesign or consolidation does not have the effect of denying eligibility for services to population groups otherwise eligible to be served under applicable Federal law; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"except that, with respect to the reallocation, consolidation, and redesign of programs described in subsection (b)(2) or (c) of , a joint agreement between the Secretary and the Indian Tribe shall be required.section 5363 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":"Retrocession","label":"e Retrocession","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"An Indian Tribe may fully or partially retrocede to the Secretary any program under a compact or funding agreement.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Effective date","label":"2 Effective date","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"Agreement","label":"A Agreement","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fe%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Unless an Indian Tribe rescinds a request for retrocession under paragraph (1), the retrocession shall become effective on the date specified by the parties in the compact or funding agreement.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"No agreement","label":"B No agreement","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fe%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e/2/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fe%2F2%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e/2/B/i/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e/2/B/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fe%2F2%2FB%2Fi%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"1 year after the date on which the request is submitted; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e/2/B/i/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e/2/B/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fe%2F2%2FB%2Fi%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the date on which the funding agreement expires; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e/2/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/e/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fe%2F2%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"such date as may be mutually agreed upon by the Secretary and the Indian Tribe.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":"Nonduplication","label":"f Nonduplication","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/f/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Ff%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"shall not be entitled to contract with the Secretary for funds under , except that the Indian Tribe shall be eligible for new programs on the same basis as other Indian Tribes; andsection 5321 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/f/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Ff%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"shall be responsible for the administration of programs in accordance with the compact or funding agreement.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"g","heading":"Records","label":"g Records","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/g","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fg","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/g/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fg%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Unless an Indian Tribe specifies otherwise in the compact or funding agreement, records of an Indian Tribe shall not be considered to be Federal records for purposes of chapter 5 of title 5.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Recordkeeping system","label":"2 Recordkeeping system","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/g/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fg%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/g/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/g/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fg%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"maintain a recordkeeping system; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/g/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5365/g/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft25%2Fs5365%2Fg%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"on a notice period of not less than 30 days, provide the Secretary with reasonable access to the records to enable the Department to meet the requirements of sections 3101 through 3106 of title 44.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
